ContentClassification.Comments: Study Data: Derived from the A75-80 Mortality Tables published in the “1986 Transactions of the Society of Actuaries, Volume 38” (pp. 205-227). Those basic tables provided sex distinct rates on both an age nearest and age last birthday basis, up to issue age 70 on a 15-year select period basis and up to attained age 100 on an ultimate age basis. The Manulife Reinsurance Extension provides mortality rates for issue ages 71 to 90 with decreasing select periods and up to the attained age 100 on an ultimate basis. A further extension from ultimate age 100 to age 105 uses the constant difference pattern implicit in the values at age 100 and immediately prior. Data Transcription Errors: None. Data Certified: 06/2019.
